{
  "stem": "1918.6",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 261.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then, finally, she said, there is a listing at that address for someone else.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, go and get them immediately.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they got the lady who had a telephone, and they called on my aunt, and my aunt talked to us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- and then they went to get my father, and my father couldn't come to get us, because he was very religious.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And those days, you took about seven hours to get by train to Baltimore.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So he couldn't get there until Sunday morning.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He started out Saturday night, and he got there Sunday morning.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we met my father.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He was an old, broken man, and we were worlds apart, he with his extreme religiosity, and we with Auschwitz in our-- our skull.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it was very, very hard to find a common ground.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was very difficult, yet he took us back to New York.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He paid for our fare.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And my sister-- there was only one Jew, one Jewish officer on the ship, and that was Jack Berman.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they fell in love, and less than four weeks later, they got married.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Chicha.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they have three kids, and she has one grandchild and two on their way, and they're still married.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and then the two of us came to New York-- well, the three of us came to New York.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then she went off and she got married, and the two of us lived with my father.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then my father got a letter in May of 19-- after we were already in America.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, the camps were liberated-- I don't know-- in April 15 or-- by the time we got word that my brother is alive, we were in America.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
